Germany’s Schaeuble Sees Little Leeway for Tax Cuts, Bild Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-06-25T10:26:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/germany-s-schaeuble-sees-little-leeway-for-tax-cuts-bild-says.html
Germany ’s Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  sees little leeway for tax cuts,  Bild  am Sonntag said
in a news release previewing tomorrow’s edition.  Budget consolidation will be more important than lowering
taxes, and the country will have to shoulder additional expenses
in coming years such as paying for a retreat from nuclear
energy, the newspaper said, citing an interview with the
politician.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in  Frankfurt  at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 